g.text: Now its the next players turn.

text.style: fill: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: Handlee; font-size: 23.3826px; font-weight: 300; line-height: 30.8825px; white-space: pre;
text.tspan: Answer incorrectly and you must pick another card
from the top of the deck and add it to your hand.

text.style: fill: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: Handlee; font-size: 23.3826px; font-weight: 300; line-height: 30.8825px; white-space: pre;
text.tspan: Answer correctly and you're free to swap one of your
cards with another player, or the deck if you wish.

text.style: fill: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: Handlee; font-size: 23.3826px; font-weight: 300; line-height: 30.8825px; white-space: pre;
text.tspan: Place the card answer face up next to the deck.

text.style: fill: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: Handlee; font-size: 23.4px; font-weight: 300; line-height: 30.8825px; white-space: pre;

g.text: On your turn select one of your cards, explain the question​and say your answer out loud.

text.style: fill: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: Handlee; font-size: 23.3826px; font-weight: 300; line-height: 30.8825px; white-space: pre;
text.tspan: Turn the card over to show the answer.

text.style: fill: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: Handlee; font-size: 23.4px; font-weight: 300; line-height: 30.8825px; white-space: pre;

g.text: The player to the left of the dealer starts.

text.style: fill: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: Handlee; font-size: 23.3826px; font-weight: 300; line-height: 30.8825px; white-space: pre;
text.tspan: No player should look at the answers, however each
player can align the cards so they are all visible.

text.style: fill: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: Handlee; font-size: 23.3826px; font-weight: 300; line-height: 30.8825px; white-space: pre;
text.tspan: Placing the cards Question up, deal 4 cards for everyone
and place the rest of the deck in the middle.

text.style: fill: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: "Bree Serif"; font-size: 43.041px; line-height: 65.4223px; white-space: pre;
text.tspan: The winner is the first player
to get rid of all their cards.
